ProtocolMsgDATA

public ProtocolMsgDATA(byte[] msg,
                       int length)
                throws ProtocolMalformedMsgException
Construct from raw bytes. Code has been removed that copies the message buffer, so beware: if you re-use "msg", you'll corrupt what's here. You can be safe by doing: byte [] newRawData = new byte[rawData.length]; System.arraycopy(rawData, 0, newRawData, 0, rawData.length); rawData = newRawData;

Parameters:
msg - The raw message bytes
length - The number of bytes in the message
